metadata.name: Morning Glow
metadata.description:
A hyena silhouette with a perfectly outlined rim light caused by the sunrise.

The hyenas usually are very active during the early morning hours. This morning, in particular, a large group of hyenas was trying to eat from the remains of a lionâ€™s food.

As one of them walked towards the food, I timed the shot for it to be right under the sun, to capture this beautiful outline.
